<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE -
        Installation - Flywheel
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Flywheel</title>
        <figure id="f2651339" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0704.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 489. Flywheel on guide pins</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two flywheel guide pins (make locally) into crankshaft flange at approximately 3
                o'clock and 9 o'clock positions.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align flywheel dowel hole with crankshaft secondary flange dowel and slide flywheel onto
                guide pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align reinforcement ring with dowel and slide over guide pins. Make sure lip on outer
                circumference of ring is facing towards the transmission.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, use new bolts to install flywheel.</para>
            </caution>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use antiseize, grease, or lubricants on flywheel bolts. Each has
                    an adverse effect on torque results.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two M10 x 77 flywheel mounting bolts to secure flywheel to crankshaft. Remove both
                guide pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install eight remaining M10 x 77 flywheel mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651340" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0739.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"
                     box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 490. Torque sequence for flexplate</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Snug all bolts in the sequence to 1 - 7 N&#183;m (12 - 60 lbf&#183;in).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Torque all bolts to the special torque and in the sequence shown below.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
